ngoList.title: Multi Vaccines Development Program
ngoList.detailsOfAchievement: Multi Vaccines Development Program is the first and one of its kind translational development program for vaccine development based in India. In last 8 years, MVDP and ICGEB in collaboration has resulted in transition of three malaria vaccine candidates (2 for P. falciparum and 1 for P. vivax) from ICGEB lab to Phase I first-in-man clinical trials. Two Phase I clinical trials have already been completed and a third with another novel P. falciparum malaria vaccine will be initiated soon.

sourceOfFunds.purpose: Multi Vaccines Development Program was established in 2010 for advancing vaccine research including conduct of clinical trials. Department of Biotechnology (DBT), International Centre for Genetic Engineering and Biotechnology (ICGEB) and Malaria Vaccine Initiative (MVI), PATH, came together to support the establishment of MVDP. ICGEB and DBT provided funding (INR 12,03,57,879/-) to establish MVDP as an independent society.

MVDP core sustenance was covered by the grant received from ICGEB. MVDP raised additional funds for malaria vaccine development projects. It received FCRA prior permission in 2012 to receive USD 8,11,023 from PATH-MVI for advancement of P. vivax malaria vaccine development. In addition, DBT provided funds for development of malaria vaccines using influenza VLP platform (INR 6,50,000) and for development of a recombinant combination blood stage vaccine for P. falciparum malaria (INR 2,90,00,000).

The core expenditures of MVDP were covered by initial grant received from ICGEB and interest of INR 2,99,22,012 that was earned on the core grant received. The interest earned supported functioning of MVDP in 2017- 2018. MVDP successfully completed the preclinical toxicology studies and initiated Phase I clinical trial with PvDBPII, a novel recombinant vaccine candidate for Plasmodium vivax. MVDP also transferred the technology for cGMP production of the P. falciparum malaria vaccines to a CMO.

MVDP continues to utilize the remaining interest money earned on the core grant for functioning of the organization and support ongoing malaria vaccine. During this period MVDP successfully completed the Phase I clinical trial with PvDBPII, a novel recombinant P. vivax vaccine candidate. Besides successfully completing preclinical toxicology studies, MVDP initiated a Phase I clinical trial with another novel recombinant P. falciparum vaccine candidate with funding support from DBT and BIRAC.

ngoList.detailsOfAchievement: Navyug Economic and Educational Development Society (NEEDS) was established on 18th July 2005, registered under Societies Registration Act XXI of 1860, u/s 12A & 80G of Income Tax Act 1961. NEEDS is a non-government, non-profit organization dedicated to undertake the socio-economic, political, educational and ecological challenges of the 21st century. NEEDS is also engaged in knowledge based activism, i.e., creating a lasting impact through intensive research and study. Its approach for socio-economic, political, cultural etc. development is grounded in high quality field research. NEEDS as an organization, draws on the knowledge and expertise of its members to undertake innovative research and study Force Behind Needs NEEDS is a humanitarian and development endeavour by a group of social workers, environmentalists, health professionals, IT professionals, engineers and economists with an urge to create healthy, vital, sustainable community. NEEDS is a partnership of motivated, articulate, determined, zestful, gregarious members committed to making our society a place to help us achieve our socio-economic, cultural and spiritual capabilities to the highest potential. NEEDS endeavour is to evolve human culture in harmony with nature. Prime Objectives The prime objective of NEEDS is to undertake, organise, co-ordinate, motivate, promote, develop and mobilize the activities and programmes focusing on two dimensions:- (a) Implementing various activities and programmes; and (b) Conducting intensive research & study on various socio-economic, cultural and developmental issues. Focus Areas Charitable activities organised by NEEDS are mainly for under privileged children and women, adolescents, senior citizens, people exposed to high risk HIV/ AIDS/ STD/ RTI, health and sanitation issues mainly in rural and slum areas, legal assistance, preservation of culture, environment and forest protection etc. NEEDS is also engaged in knowledge based activism, i.e., creating a lasting impact through intensive research and study. The members and associates of NEEDS have undertaken several studies in different fields and NEEDS as an organization draws on the knowledge and expertise of its members to undertake innovative research and study in the area of socio-economic, cultural, spiritual and overall development. The main thrust areas of NEEDS include the following:- Health and Nutrition. Literacy and Education. Preservation of Indian Art, Culture and Heritage. Promote, Foster and Protect Buddhism. Women and Child Development. Rural Development. Environment Protection and Sanitation. Legal Awareness and Human Rights. Road and Transport. NEEDS organized many awareness programs, workshops and rallies emphasizing the importance of education. For overall development of a person in particular and society in general, education plays a very important role. Realising this fact, NEEDS gives emphasis on providing education to each and every individual so that they can achieve their goals/targets and hence connect them with the development and growth of the nation. NEEDS performed the â€˜Road showâ€™ of several cultural programmes and stage programmes to spread their vision to the illiterates. NEEDS has a program to generate awareness about the preservation of our art and cultural heritage. India is a land of diverse cultures with an immense physical, religious, racial and linguistic variety. It is due to variations in geographical, climatic conditions and due to influence from outsiders, whether invaders or colonizers. Greatness of India has been in accepting the customs and traditions of others and inter-mingling them with the existing. This is visible in all aspects viz; music, dance, painting, sculptures, architecture, arts and crafts, fairs and festivals, languages and literature, cuisine, social customs, ceremonies and traditions, religions, rituals, artifacts, monuments etc. NEEDS organise cultural activities and programmes to promote the art and culture. NEEDS promote Art and culture through play and stabilising library to spread the cultural heritage. NEEDS promote the Art, culture and heritage through audio and visual CDs. NEEDS is interacting with women to attend several programmes performed by it. They have joined hands with us to improve their social status in the society. NEEDS is taking care to spread education, awareness about the pitfalls of foetus infanticide and female foeticide, child marriage, purda system, domestic violence, omission of the rights of widows and other disparities in society with them. NEEDS is committed to promote respect and dignity to women. Prevention of Domestic Violence Act has come as a huge relief for women but the Act will serve its purpose only if it is implemented in the right spirit. Even in the 21st century representation of women parliament and state assemblies is very nominal. We must harness all support we can get to attain political empowerment of women. Inheritance judgements in favour of distribution of ancestral property to women is a welcome decision of the Supreme Court. It has been the consistent policy of NEEDS to strive for right representation of women on its entire educational, professional and other platforms in the society. NEEDS is keen to insure the development of livelihood among rural community. To support rural people we conduct informative seminar and workshop; provide informative education and early child education in rural areas, incorporating the local people by undertaking constructive works like village level micro planning, environment conservation through members of Gram Sabha. NEEDS helps the underprivileged sections of the society. It is progressing slowly but steadily and successfully achieving goals and targets through various programmes:- HIV / AIDS Awareness Campaign Perfect Life Line Health Project Sarva Jan Siksha Abhiyan. Sampoorn Mahila Vikas Abhiyan. Preservation/Promotion of Indian Art, Culture and Heritage. Promote, Foster and Protect Buddhism. Road Safety Programmes.

Social & Human Development a) Community Development The Association has been working with underprivileged people living in slums and resettlement colonies with the motto to develop a self-reliant society by educating and motivating them. At present, community work is being carried out at eleven Alternative learning centers coordinated through Five Basti Vikas Kendraâ€™s at Karpoori Thakur, Kalyanpuri and Sunlight colony Concentrating on child care, community health care, womenâ€™s welfare, adult Education, legal assistance, literacy and income generating Programme. The Association through its Awareness Generation Camps make the group of The women from the community aware on issues related to health and hygiene, Nutrition, legal rights and advocacy, empowerment, education, gender & HIV. The camps are partly supported by the Delhi Social Welfare Advisory Board. The Association through its Family Counselling Centre at Aradhak Nagar Addressees various issues concerning Dowry harassment, dowry death, Cruelty, Bigamy, personality differences and behavioral problems in children. II. Centre for Development of Youth and Challenged (CDYC) a) Special School The center is contributing to the needs of the youth and the challenged in and Around the Nizamuddin through its Special School & Home Training Programme. Special School is an effort towards physical, social and Psychological development of the mentally retarded children and helps to Build among them a positive self-image. III. Rural Community Development Centre (RCDC) New Delhi YMCA has a Rural Development Centre a village Bulwana, Hodal. The Centre is working in 12 villages in Hodal Block. Through these centers have Programmes on literacy, community health and skill training for women and girls are conducted. Self Help Groups are formed in the Hodal to make the women independent and self-reliant. Illiterate ladies and girls in the villages are made literate and taught the basics of tailoring, embroidery and preventive maintenance of machines. IV. Education & Human Potential Development The Association through its Human Potential Development Programme provides quality education to young persons in diverse areas, ranging from Primary School to under graduate level Programmes. Office Management and Career Studies Programs are providing employment oriented undergraduate programs. The Media Studies and Management proving, to post graduate level Programme in Management and Media Studies. V. Medical Relief Activities carried on to provide medical relief by treating patients either with or Without charges are considered as charitable purpose. It may be noted that the activity need not be absolutely philanthropic, in the sense that one has to provide Free medical services or subsidized medical services. Further, New Delhi YMCA runs comprehensive health and healthy life promotional Programs. Under this program New Delhi YMCA is running Clinics for every Community development centers (CDC) in all over Delhi including RCDC Hodal. The Association has conducted workshop on â€˜Awareness of HIV / AIDS â€˜to generate Awareness on HIV / AIDS with the students. Free Eye camps, eye operations and general medical camps are organized each year. These programs are organized to give free medical assistance to the people from economically weaker section of the society.
